<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-04-21T13:54:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-04-21T13:54:00-05:00" n="752" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d752">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">890F.51/71: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister Resident in Saudi Arabia</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Moose</hi></persName>)
                                    <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Jidda</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-04-21T22:00:00+03:06">April
                                        21, 1944—10 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received April 22—11:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>118. My 114, April 18, 5 p.m. While Jordan was in King’s camp King
                                repeated request for written statement of intended British aid to
                                Saudi Arabia and said if adequate assistance could not be had from
                                British he would appeal to oil company or American Government.</p>
                            <p>Jordan was unable to give desired statement but promised to secure
                                data in Cairo and to answer when he and General Paget visit King at
                                Riyadh about April 26.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Moose</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>